   <note>Benjamin, a man of color, by next friend William Miller vs. Simmons, James G. Hawkins County Chancery Court. Miller argues for the freedom of Benjamin, a slave who was owned by Simmons, now deceased. Miller claims that Simmons raised Ben as child rather than a slave. Simmons evidently gave Ben his freedom in his will upon Simmons death.</note>
